slots.description: Appends rows to the table's `<tbody>`

slots.title: footer prepend

slots.description: Targets all the headers inside `<tfoot>`. Works if there's a `footer-clone` prop set to `true`

slots.name: footerAppend
slots.title: footer append
slots.description: Appends rows to the `<tfoot>`

props.name: columns
props.title: columns

props.name: items
props.title: items
props.description: Array of objects with table data (`ITableItem: Record<string, any>`). The `va-data-table` automatically calculates the amount and the titles of columns (if not specified otherwise with the `columns` prop) based on these object's keys. When calculating the columns' names based on the item's objects' keys `va-data-table` uses [Lodash's startCase](https://lodash.com/docs/4.17.15#startCase)[[target=_blank]] internally. Faulty values are replaced with an empty string

props.name: filter
props.title: filter
props.description: If a `filter` is provided, only rows in which at least one cell contains the specified value will be displayed. To disable filtering at runtime (clear `filter`), specify an empty string

props.name: filterMethod
props.title: filter method
props.description: A custom filtering function. The function takes the initial value of the currently checked cell (the `source` is a formal parameter) and should return a `boolean` value, indicating whether to include the row containing this cell or not

props.name: sortBy
props.title: sort by
props.description: Sets the column to sort by. Works through the `v-model`

props.name: sortingOrder
props.title: sorting order
props.description: Sets the sorting order. Works through the `v-model`

props.name: selectable
props.title: selectable
props.description: Sets whether the `va-data-table` should have selectable rows or not

props.name: clickable
props.title: clickable
props.description: Sets whether the `va-data-table` should have clickable (the click events will be emitted) rows or not

props.name: selectMode
props.title: select mode
props.description: Sets the select mode. `'single'` selection allows for only a single row to be selected at a time, while `'multiple'` mode allows to select multiple rows by clicking on checkboxes or using the **ctrl**/**shift** keys when clicking rows

props.name: selectedColor
props.title: selected color
props.description: Sets the highlighting color of the selected row

props.name: perPage
props.title: per page
props.description: Sets the maximum number of rows displayed in the table's `<tbody>`

props.name: currentPage
props.title: current page
props.description: Sets the number of the current table page

props.name: loading
props.title: loading
props.description: Sets the loading state for the table (by displaying the spinning loading-indicator)

props.name: loadingColor
props.title: loading color
props.description: Sets the color of the spinning loading-indicator

props.name: noDataHtml
props.title: no data html
props.description: Sets html-content for cases where there are no items passed in the `items` option at all

props.name: noDataFilteredHtml
props.title: no data filtered html
props.description: Sets html-content for cases where there are no items found when filtering the table using the `filter` prop
props.default: No items match the provided filtering condition

props.name: hideDefaultHeader
props.title: hide default header
props.description: Sets whether to show the default headers for columns

props.name: footerClone
props.title: footer clone
props.description: Sets whether to clone the `<thead>` columns into the `<tfoot>`. Has no effect if the default `<thead>` is hidden with the `hide-default-header` prop

props.name: allowFooterSorting
props.title: allow footer sorting
props.description: Allows clicks on `<tfoot>` column headers to sort (and to display the sorting status) the rows

props.name: striped
props.title: striped
props.description: Sets the striped style to the `<tbody>` rows (highlights each 2nd row)

props.name: hoverable
props.title: hoverable
props.description: Allows the hover state on table rows within a `<tbody>`. The highlighting color of the hover state takes from `selected-color` prop

props.name: animated
props.title: animated
props.description: Sets css `transition` to table rows

props.name: stickyHeader
props.title: sticky header
props.description: Enables sticky header (sticky header is achieved through CSS with `position: sticky` for `thead`)

props.name: height
props.title: height
props.description: Sets the height to the table and enables scrolling
